Different from Western world, there are many dialects area by area in Japan. <br>
The main reason is explained by Amanohashidate. <br>
But the differences in dialects were accelarated by the restriction policies of local rulers on the people's move beyond the boundaries of areas in the samurai ara.<br>
Those rulers repeated fighting one another aiming at invading the other's territory to expand each own territory. <br>
You like &quot;NINJA&quot; that were specialized spies to collect information and report about the area its master ruler wanted to invade and occupy, so that the ruler's army could carry the attack efficiently. <br>
The aimed-at ruler side had to detect such strangers from outside of its territory to protect its territory from such invaders. <br>
The farther the distance between areas,  the difference in dialects had become bigger. <br>
The easiest and most efficient way to detect such stranger was by the dialect he speaks. <br>
So, the feudal lords supported the governmental policy of restricting strictly the peoples move over the different areas without official permissions of local governments.<br>
